cbsHardwareMIB.name: cbsHardwareMIB

revisions.description: Added bootwait state to hardware module status.
Added separate objects for AC & DC power supply/feed.
Added Trap definitions for DBHA link up/down.

cbsHardwareMIB.contactinfo: Email: mib-admin@crossbeamsys.com Postal: 200 Baker Avenue Concord MA 01742
cbsHardwareMIB.description: This MIB module defines the objects to identify and monitor Crossbeam Systems hardware.

OperationalState.name: OperationalState
OperationalState.description: The operational state of a hardware subsystem.

cbsHwSystemDescription.name: cbsHwSystemDescription
cbsHwSystemDescription.description: A textual description of the product.

cbsHwSystemSerialNumber.name: cbsHwSystemSerialNumber
cbsHwSystemSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the system.

cbsHwSystemBackplaneRevision.name: cbsHwSystemBackplaneRevision
cbsHwSystemBackplaneRevision.description: The Revision of the system backplane.

cbsHwSystemRedundentPowerSupplyStatus.name: cbsHwSystemRedundentPowerSupplyStatus
cbsHwSystemRedundentPowerSupplyStatus.description: Indicates that the redundent power supply is operational. This object is obsoleted in favor of separate objects for AC and DC power supply.

cbsHwSystemRedundentPowerFeedStatus.name: cbsHwSystemRedundentPowerFeedStatus
cbsHwSystemRedundentPowerFeedStatus.description: Indicates that both of the redundent backplane power feeds are operational. This object is obsoleted in favor of separate objects for AC and DC power feed.

cbsHwSystemChassisTemp.name: cbsHwSystemChassisTemp
cbsHwSystemChassisTemp.description: The temperature of the chassis air flow as measured at the upper fan tray.

cbsHwSystemUpperFanTray.name: cbsHwSystemUpperFanTray
cbsHwSystemUpperFanTray.description: The upper fan tray is present in the system.

cbsHwSystemLowerFanTray.name: cbsHwSystemLowerFanTray
cbsHwSystemLowerFanTray.description: The lower fan tray is present in the system.

cbsHwSystemAlarm.name: cbsHwSystemAlarm
cbsHwSystemAlarm.description: Indicates the highest current alarm state of the system.

cbsHwSystemPowerType.name: cbsHwSystemPowerType
cbsHwSystemPowerType.description: Indicates the power type of the system.

cbsHwSystemRedundentACPowerSupplyStatus.name: cbsHwSystemRedundentACPowerSupplyStatus
cbsHwSystemRedundentACPowerSupplyStatus.description: Indicates that the redundent AC power supply is operational. Will return down (i.e. not-operational) for DC chassis.

cbsHwSystemRedundentACPowerFeedStatus.name: cbsHwSystemRedundentACPowerFeedStatus
cbsHwSystemRedundentACPowerFeedStatus.description: Indicates that both of the redundent backplane AC power feeds are operational. Will return down (i.e. not-operational) for DC chassis.

cbsHwSystemDCPowerFilterA.name: cbsHwSystemDCPowerFilterA
cbsHwSystemDCPowerFilterA.description: Indicates if DC power filter A is present or not present. Will return not present for AC chassis.

cbsHwSystemDCPowerFilterB.name: cbsHwSystemDCPowerFilterB
cbsHwSystemDCPowerFilterB.description: Indicates if DC power filter B is present or not present. Will return not present for AC chassis.

cbsHwSystemDCPowerFeedA.name: cbsHwSystemDCPowerFeedA
cbsHwSystemDCPowerFeedA.description: Indicates if DC power feed A is present or not present. Will return not present for AC chassis.

cbsHwSystemDCPowerFeedB.name: cbsHwSystemDCPowerFeedB
cbsHwSystemDCPowerFeedB.description: Indicates if DC power feed B is present or not present. Will return not present for AC chassis.

cbsFanStatusTable.name: cbsFanStatusTable
cbsFanStatusTable.description: This table contains information about the fan trays currently installed in the system.

cbsFanStatusEntry.name: cbsFanStatusEntry
cbsFanStatusEntry.description: An entry in the hardware module table.

cbsFanIndex.name: cbsFanIndex
cbsFanIndex.description: The fan number in the fan tray.

cbsHwModuleTable.name: cbsHwModuleTable
cbsHwModuleTable.description: This table contains information about the processor modules currently installed in the system.

cbsHwModuleEntry.name: cbsHwModuleEntry
cbsHwModuleEntry.description: An entry in the hardware module table.

cbsHwModuleID.name: cbsHwModuleID
cbsHwModuleID.description: The product ID for the module.

cbsHwModuleProductID.name: cbsHwModuleProductID
cbsHwModuleProductID.description: The product ID for the module.

cbsHwModuleDescription.name: cbsHwModuleDescription
cbsHwModuleDescription.description: A short description of the module.

cbsHwModuleBoardRevision.name: cbsHwModuleBoardRevision
cbsHwModuleBoardRevision.description: The board revision level of the module.

cbsHwModuleSerialNumber.name: cbsHwModuleSerialNumber
cbsHwModuleSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the module.

cbsHwModuleBootStrapRev.name: cbsHwModuleBootStrapRev
cbsHwModuleBootStrapRev.description: Total static DRAM memory on the module in Kilobytes.

cbsHwModuleBootloaderRev.name: cbsHwModuleBootloaderRev
cbsHwModuleBootloaderRev.description: Total static DRAM memory on the module in Kilobytes.

cbsHwModuleDiagnosticsRev.name: cbsHwModuleDiagnosticsRev
cbsHwModuleDiagnosticsRev.description: Total static DRAM memory on the module in Kilobytes.

cbsHwModuleSDRAMSize.name: cbsHwModuleSDRAMSize
cbsHwModuleSDRAMSize.description: Total Static DRAM memory on the module in Kilobytes.

cbsHwModuleRDRAMSize.name: cbsHwModuleRDRAMSize
cbsHwModuleRDRAMSize.description: Total RDRAM memory on the module in Kilobytes.

cbsHwModuleDiskAPresent.name: cbsHwModuleDiskAPresent
cbsHwModuleDiskAPresent.description: The first disk storage device is present.

cbsHwModuleDiskBPresent.name: cbsHwModuleDiskBPresent
cbsHwModuleDiskBPresent.description: The second disk storage device is present.

cbsHwModuleDuartAPresent.name: cbsHwModuleDuartAPresent
cbsHwModuleDuartAPresent.description: The first DUART device is present on the module.

cbsHwModuleDuartBPresent.name: cbsHwModuleDuartBPresent
cbsHwModuleDuartBPresent.description: The second DUART device is present on the module.

cbsHwModuleAccelCard1Present.name: cbsHwModuleAccelCard1Present
cbsHwModuleAccelCard1Present.description: The Accelerator Card 1 is present on the module.

cbsHwModuleAccelCard2Present.name: cbsHwModuleAccelCard2Present
cbsHwModuleAccelCard2Present.description: The Accelerator Card 2 is present on the module.

cbsHwComponentRevTable.name: cbsHwComponentRevTable
cbsHwComponentRevTable.description: A table containing the revision level of programable hardware components.

cbsHwComponentRevEntry.name: cbsHwComponentRevEntry
cbsHwComponentRevEntry.description: An entry in the hardware component revision table.

cbsHwComponentRevision.name: cbsHwComponentRevision
cbsHwComponentRevision.description: Revision level of the programable component

cbsHwModuleStatusTable.name: cbsHwModuleStatusTable
cbsHwModuleStatusTable.description: This table contains the status of processor modules currently installed in the system.

cbsHwModuleStatusEntry.name: cbsHwModuleStatusEntry
cbsHwModuleStatusEntry.description: An entry in the hardware module status table.

cbsHwModuleStatus.name: cbsHwModuleStatus
cbsHwModuleStatus.description: The operational state of the module unavailable - No status is currently available for this module. down - The module is currently down. initializing - The module is loading. up - The module is in an operational state. standby - The module is operating in standby mode. bootwait - The module is waiting for resources to become available so it can load software.

cbsHwModuleCpuTemp.name: cbsHwModuleCpuTemp
cbsHwModuleCpuTemp.description: The current CPU temperature in degrees centigrade.

cbsHwModuleFPGATemp.name: cbsHwModuleFPGATemp
cbsHwModuleFPGATemp.description: The current FPGA temperature in degrees centigrade.

cbsHwModuleInTemp.name: cbsHwModuleInTemp
cbsHwModuleInTemp.description: The current temperature at the sensor located at the bottom of the board in degrees centigrade.

cbsHwModuleInTempAlarm.name: cbsHwModuleInTempAlarm
cbsHwModuleInTempAlarm.description: Indicates a high temperature alarm for the bottom board sensor.

cbsHwModuleExhaustTemp.name: cbsHwModuleExhaustTemp
cbsHwModuleExhaustTemp.description: The current temperature at the sensor located at the top of the board in degrees centigrade.

cbsHwModuleExhaustTempAlarm.name: cbsHwModuleExhaustTempAlarm
cbsHwModuleExhaustTempAlarm.description: Indicates a high temperature alarm for the top board sensor.

cbsHwModuleCPUVoltage.name: cbsHwModuleCPUVoltage
cbsHwModuleCPUVoltage.description: The current voltage level of the processor supply. This number is in 1/100ths of a volt and the ideal value depends on the speed of the processor.

cbsHwModule1_8Voltage.name: cbsHwModule1_8Voltage
cbsHwModule1_8Voltage.description: The current voltage level of the 1.8 volt power supply. This number is in 1/100ths of a volt and the ideal value of 1.8 volts will be read as 180.

cbsHwModule3_3Voltage.name: cbsHwModule3_3Voltage
cbsHwModule3_3Voltage.description: The current voltage level of the 3.3 volt power supply. This number is in 1/100ths of a volt and the ideal value of 3.3 volts will be read as 330.

cbsHwModule2_5Voltage.name: cbsHwModule2_5Voltage
cbsHwModule2_5Voltage.description: The current voltage level of the 2.5 volt power supply. This number is in 1/100ths of a volt and the ideal value of 2.5 volts will be read as 250.

cbsHwModuleControlLinkA.name: cbsHwModuleControlLinkA
cbsHwModuleControlLinkA.description: The operation state of control link A.

cbsHwModuleControlLinkB.name: cbsHwModuleControlLinkB
cbsHwModuleControlLinkB.description: The Operational state of control link B.

cbsHwModuleActiveLED.name: cbsHwModuleActiveLED
cbsHwModuleActiveLED.description: Indicates the board's active LED is on.

cbsHwModuleStandbyLED.name: cbsHwModuleStandbyLED
cbsHwModuleStandbyLED.description: Indicates the board's standby LED is on.

cbsHwModuleFailedLED.name: cbsHwModuleFailedLED
cbsHwModuleFailedLED.description: Indicates the board's failed LED is on.

cbsHwModuleCpu2Temp.name: cbsHwModuleCpu2Temp
cbsHwModuleCpu2Temp.description: For dual processor modules, 2nd CPU's current temperature in degrees centigrade. For modules that don't support it, a special invalid value of 10000 will be returned.

cbsHwModuleCPU2Voltage.name: cbsHwModuleCPU2Voltage
cbsHwModuleCPU2Voltage.description: For dual processor modules, 2nd CPU's current voltage level. This number is in 1/100ths of a volt and the ideal value depends on the speed of the processor. For modules that don't support it, a special invalid value of 10000 will be returned.

cbsHwModuleFPGA1_8Voltage.name: cbsHwModuleFPGA1_8Voltage
cbsHwModuleFPGA1_8Voltage.description: FPGA's current voltage level of the 1.8 volt power supply. This number is in 1/100ths of a volt and the ideal value of 1.8 volts will be read as 180. For modules that don't support it, a special invalid value of 10000 will be returned.

cbsHwModule125Voltage.name: cbsHwModule125Voltage
cbsHwModule125Voltage.description: Current voltage level of the 1.25 volt power supply. This number is in 1/100ths of a volt and the ideal value of 1.25 volts will be read as 125. For modules that don't support it, a special invalid value of 10000 will be returned.

cbsHwSdpStatusTable.name: cbsHwSdpStatusTable
cbsHwSdpStatusTable.description: Table containing status of the Switched Data Path backplane links.

cbsHwSdpStatusEntry.name: cbsHwSdpStatusEntry
cbsHwSdpStatusEntry.description: An entry in the hardware SDP status table.

cbsHwSdpNpmSlot.name: cbsHwSdpNpmSlot
cbsHwSdpNpmSlot.description: The slot number of the Network Processor Module end of the link

cbsHwSdpRemoteSlot.name: cbsHwSdpRemoteSlot
cbsHwSdpRemoteSlot.description: The slot number of the remote end of the link

cbsHwSdpNpmState.name: cbsHwSdpNpmState
cbsHwSdpNpmState.description: The operational state of the NPM side of the link.

cbsHwSdpRemoteState.name: cbsHwSdpRemoteState
cbsHwSdpRemoteState.description: The operational state of the remote end of the link.

cbsHwPowerSupplyFailed.name: cbsHwPowerSupplyFailed
cbsHwPowerSupplyFailed.description: One of the redundent power supplies or DC filters has failed or been removed.

cbsHwPowerSupplyRecovered.name: cbsHwPowerSupplyRecovered
cbsHwPowerSupplyRecovered.description: A redundent power supply or DC filter that was previously failed or missing has been replaced.

cbsHwPowerFeedFailed.name: cbsHwPowerFeedFailed
cbsHwPowerFeedFailed.description: One of the redundent backplane power feed has failed.

cbsHwPowerFeedRecovered.name: cbsHwPowerFeedRecovered
cbsHwPowerFeedRecovered.description: One of the redundent backplane power feed that previously not working has become operational.

cbsHwUpperFanTrayInserted.name: cbsHwUpperFanTrayInserted
cbsHwUpperFanTrayInserted.description: A fan tray has been inserted into the system.

cbsHwUpperFanTrayRemoved.name: cbsHwUpperFanTrayRemoved
cbsHwUpperFanTrayRemoved.description: A fan tray has been removed from the system.

cbsHwLowerFanTrayInserted.name: cbsHwLowerFanTrayInserted
cbsHwLowerFanTrayInserted.description: A fan tray has been inserted into the system.

cbsHwLowerFanTrayRemoved.name: cbsHwLowerFanTrayRemoved
cbsHwLowerFanTrayRemoved.description: A fan tray has been removed from the system.

cbsHwFanFailed.name: cbsHwFanFailed
cbsHwFanFailed.description: One of the system cooling fans has failed.

cbsHwFanRecovered.name: cbsHwFanRecovered
cbsHwFanRecovered.description: A Fan that was inoperative has recovered.

cbsHwSystemAlarmTrap.name: cbsHwSystemAlarmTrap
cbsHwSystemAlarmTrap.description: Indicates that the alarm state of the system has changed.

cbsHwChassisTempExceeded.name: cbsHwChassisTempExceeded
cbsHwChassisTempExceeded.description: Indicates the the chassis temperature, as measure at the exhaust fan has exceeded the maximum.

cbsHwChassisTempNormal.name: cbsHwChassisTempNormal
cbsHwChassisTempNormal.description: Indicates the the chassis temperature, as measure at the exhaust fan has returned to normal.

cbsHwModuleStatusChanged.name: cbsHwModuleStatusChanged
cbsHwModuleStatusChanged.description: The status of a processor module has changed, the new status of the module that has changed is reported.

cbsHwModuleInserted.name: cbsHwModuleInserted
cbsHwModuleInserted.description: A processor module been inserted into the system, reports the slot number of the module that has been inserted.

cbsHwModuleRemoved.name: cbsHwModuleRemoved
cbsHwModuleRemoved.description: A processor module been removed into the system, reports the slot number of the module that has been removed.

cbsModuleTempExceeded.name: cbsModuleTempExceeded
cbsModuleTempExceeded.description: Indicates that the module CPU temperature has execeeded the high limit.

cbsModuleTempNormal.name: cbsModuleTempNormal
cbsModuleTempNormal.description: Indicates that the module CPU temperature has returned to the normal operating range.

cbsDbhaLinkUp.name: cbsDbhaLinkUp
cbsDbhaLinkUp.description: The DBHA link on this CPM has come up.

cbsDbhaLinkDown.name: cbsDbhaLinkDown
cbsDbhaLinkDown.description: The DBHA link on this CPM has failed.
